<P>
Bloomingdale's Hires Advisers: Bloomingdale's, the ritzy department store chain 
put up for sale by its cash-strapped Canadian parent, Campeau Corp., said it 
has hired the Blackstone Group and Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. to assist 
"senior management in evaluating its alternatives." Marvin Traub, chairman of 
Bloomingdale's, also said the chain hired Gotshal &amp; Manges as legal counsel 
to assist senior management. 
</P>
